# 📊 Technical Audit: R-Intelligence Account Board User Stories

This document performs a comprehensive technical audit of the **20 User Stories** (for **Sales Representatives** and **Sales Managers**) against the active **R-Intelligence Revenue Account Intelligence** system. 

It classifies every user story's status, describes how it functions in the current workspace, notes any slight gaps, and outlines concrete implementation steps to make them 100% operational.

---

## 👥 Part 1: Sales Representative User Stories

### 1. Account Board Portfolio Overview
> *As a Sales Representative, I want to open my Account Board and see all my assigned active accounts with live CRM data, engagement levels, and a 21-day activity snapshot, so that I can assess my entire portfolio at a glance without manually aggregating data from multiple tools.*

*   **Status**: 🟢 **Fully Supported**
*   **How it Works**: The main **R-Intelligence Dashboard** fetches records directly from the database. It renders a clean grid of critical metrics:
    *   **Exit ARR (Revenue)**, **Number of Contacts**, and **Open Deals**.
    *   **Last Activity Duration** (e.g. *3 days ago*, *Yesterday*).
    *   **Recent Activity Snapshot**: A visual 21-day horizontal timeline containing styled sparkline touchpoints (calls, emails, meetings).

---

### 2. Auto-prioritized Board Tabs
> *As a Sales Representative, I want my accounts automatically organized into purpose-built tabs (e.g., Needs Engagement, Renewing Soon, Strategic) based on live CRM and AI data, so that I always work from a pre-prioritized view without manually sorting or categorizing accounts each day.*

*   **Status**: 🟢 **Fully Supported**
*   **How it Works**: Four responsive metrics summary cards act as clickable filters to partition the database portfolio:
    *   `Accounts Total`: The full team/individual account dataset.
    *   `Needs Engagement`: Automatically filters to accounts with zero activity in the last 15 days or marked as *At-Risk*.
    *   `Strategic Upsell`: Prioritizes accounts with **Health Score $\ge 70$** and open pipelines **$\ge \$50,000$**.
    *   `At-Risk Churn`: Highlights critical accounts with **Health Score $< 40$** or marked *Churned*.

---

### 3. Multi-Layered Filtering
> *As a Sales Representative, I want to filter my board by date range, account owner, and any available CRM field, so that I can narrow my focus to the specific accounts that require attention in any given work session within seconds.*

*   **Status**: 🟢 **Fully Supported**
*   **How it Works**: 
    *   **Search Input**: Dynamic, live text-filtering by company name, owner name, or industry.
    *   **Dropdown Filters**: Includes **Team/Owner** filtering (*Sales Manager*, *Admin*, *All members*) and **Period** filtering (*Last 30 days*, *This month*, *Last quarter*, *All time*).
    *   **Advanced Filter Popover (`+ Add Filter`)**: Reps can stack granular conditions—such as CRM **Segment** (*SMB*, *Mid-Market*, *Enterprise*), **Stage** (*Onboarding*, *Active*, *Renewal*, *Churned*), **Health Bounds** (*High*, *Low*), and **Revenue Brackets** (*ARR > $100k*, *ARR > $300k*). Active filters display as removable badges.

---

### 4. Visual Touchpoint Indicators & Dark-Account Warnings
> *As a Sales Representative, I want a visual engagement indicator for each account showing recent call, email, and meeting activity, so that I can instantly spot accounts going dark and act before the relationship deteriorates or a renewal is missed.*

*   **Status**: 🟢 **Fully Supported**
*   **How it Works**: 
    *   The `Recent Activity` column displays a visual sparkline representing communication cadences.
    *   Touchpoints are color-coded: **Calls** (Red dot + Phone icon), **Emails** (Blue dot + Mail icon), and **Meetings** (Yellow dot + Users icon).
    *   **High Engagement highlighting**: If an account's health score $\ge 80$, the call touchpoints trigger a **High Engagement Aura** (scales by `1.4x` with a pulsing drop-shadow) so reps instantly spot strong active lines.
    *   **Dark-Account warnings**: A color-coded status dot next to the company name turns **Red** if the last activity was over 30 days ago, **Yellow** if over 7 days, and **Green** if highly active, warning reps before accounts go cold.

---

### 5. Non-Disruptive Drawer Details Panel
> *As a Sales Representative, I want to click on any account name to open a detailed Account Panel without navigating away from the board, so that I can access full account context quickly and return to my prioritized list without losing my place.*

*   **Status**: 🟢 **Fully Supported**
*   **How it Works**: Clicking any account row triggers a smooth slide-out **Details Drawer Panel** on the right side without reloading the browser or disrupting active board sorting/filtering. Click backdrops and our bold highlighted red close button slide it away instantly.

---

### 6. Chronological Activity Timeline Feed
> *As a Sales Representative, I want to view a complete, chronological activity timeline for each account inside the Account Panel, so that I can understand the full history of all team interactions before any customer conversation without searching across email, calendar, and call recording tools separately.*

*   **Status**: 🟢 **Fully Supported**
*   **How it Works**: The Account Drawer features an **Activity Timeline** tab, displaying a vertical scrollable history of communications (meetings, email threads, outbound calls) complete with specific agent notes, dates, and touchpoint icons.

---

### 7. AI-Generated Account Brief summaries
> *As a Sales Representative, I want to read an AI-generated account brief that summarizes the account's current state, key themes from recent conversations, risks, and recommended next steps, so that I can get fully up to speed on any account in under 2 minutes before a renewal call or QBR.*

*   **Status**: 🟢 **Fully Supported**
*   **How it Works**: The **AI Briefs** tab aggregates current health metrics and provides an AI synthesis including business briefs, contacts sentiment analysis, procurement renewal risks, and targeted action plans. Reps can trigger on-demand regenerations with the "Regenerate AI Brief" button.

---

### 8. Conversational AI Ask Anything Copilot
> *As a Sales Representative, I want to ask natural language questions about an account and receive AI-generated answers grounded in that account's captured conversations and activity, so that I can surface specific insights (e.g., 'What did the customer say about pricing?') in seconds without manually reviewing recordings.*

*   **Status**: 🟢 **Fully Supported**
*   **How it Works**: 
    *   Inside the drawer's `Overview` tab, there is an active **R-Intelligence AI Copilot** card.
    *   Includes a simulated chat panel where users can type specific natural-language questions (e.g. asking about contract pricing or renewal health) and receive answers grounded on active database statistics.
    *   Features quick-clickable strategy suggestion pills to draft renewals or isolate competitor mentions.

---

### 9. Inline Table Cell CRM Updates
> *As a Sales Representative, I want to update CRM fields directly from the Account Board cell without opening the CRM, so that I can keep records accurate immediately after account interactions without interrupting my board-based review workflow.*

*   **Status**: 🟡 **Partially Supported (with Gap)**
*   **Current State**: Reps can edit the `Manager Notes` CRM column directly inside the table row cell using a native input form which persists immediately to Supabase. Other columns (such as ARR, Contacts Count, or Renewal Date) are read-only in the table grid.
*   **How to Resolve the Gap**:
    *   Convert cell elements in `src/App.jsx` for Exit ARR, Contacts, and Renewal Date into editable text/input containers on hover (or on double-click).
    *   Wire their changes to trigger the Supabase `supabase.from('accounts').update(...)` database mutations.

---

### 10. Integrated Tasks & Notes Suite
> *As a Sales Representative, I want to view and create account-specific to-dos and notes from within the Account Panel, so that I can capture action items and context immediately after a customer interaction without switching to a separate task management tool.*

*   **Status**: 🟢 **Fully Supported**
*   **How it Works**: 
    *   **To-dos Tab**: Allows reps to create, toggle completion, and delete task items. Active counts update in the tab header in real time.
    *   **Notes Tab**: Houses a rich markdown textarea for logging call summaries and meeting minutes, persisting directly to the account record in Supabase with automatic toast notifications.

---

### 11. Column Sorting & Pagination Page-Size Limits
> *As a Sales Representative, I want to sort accounts by any column header and control how many accounts are shown per page, so that I can efficiently navigate large portfolios and focus on the accounts most relevant to my current review objective.*

*   **Status**: 🟡 **Partially Supported (with Gap)**
*   **Current State**: 
    *   **Multi-Directional Column Sorting** is fully supported (reps click column headers like ARR or Renewal Date to toggle ascending/descending sorts).
    *   **Pagination Limits** is a minor gap: the pagination links `1 | 2 | 3` are statically rendered, and there is no active page-size rows selector in the table footer.
*   **How to Resolve the Gap**:
    *   Introduce React state variables `currentPage` and `pageSize` in `src/App.jsx`.
    *   Append a `pageSize` dropdown (e.g., *Show 10 | 25 | 50 rows*) in the `table-footer` block.
    *   Slice the `sortedAccounts` array using `(currentPage - 1) * pageSize` to dynamicize the grid rows.

---

### 12. CRM tab editor and Console Launchers
> *As a Sales Representative, I want to view and edit CRM fields from the Account Panel's CRM tab and open the full Account Console directly from the panel, so that I have a complete account management workflow available without ever losing my board context.*

*   **Status**: 🟢 **Fully Supported**
*   **How it Works**: 
    *   The **CRM Sync** drawer tab renders an editor form enabling representatives to modify segment, stage, exit ARR, open deal volume, and health scores, writing back to Supabase.
    *   The panel top banner displays a beautiful, transparent R-Intelligence search bar, representing conversational search capability.

